 things.<br><br>And of course, if you are chatty and into role-playing, the cleric offers a lot of opportunity to do so, since you tend to have more typing time than the other classes, even in a no-down-time situation.<br><br>Finally, there is the whole &quot;helping people&quot; thing, which appeals to many.  The warrior or enchanter may get the glory in battle, but ask any high-level character to name their favorite person on the server and it'll be a cleric, simply because they remember that tense hour-long CR where the cleric saved them three day's worth of experience.<br><br>As for mercenary clerics?  Well, we dwarves tend to think of it as business expenses.  As in &quot;I'm just a simple business man.  I will do for you this favor. Some day, and that day may never come, I will call upon you to do a service for me....&quot;<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 9:52:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1061.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mercanary Clerics</span><hr size=1> You are right, post 50 when the exp grind is just to much like work it's a big deal to lose exp. An unrezed death can easily equate to 8 hours of exp loss. I think I was around 55 when I decided to invest in a cleric. 3 days played later I had a 49 rez-o-matic. Needing only to die 10 times to recoup the investment was an easy enough task. I think I'd have to go that route here as well, given the population and the unlikelihood of finding a cleric when you need one. The last thing I'd do would be to come to the market square looking for a cleric low enough to sell the service.  <p></p><i></i></